text: Eevamari Rauhamäki (born 23 February 1982) is a Finnish biathlete. She competed in the 2014/15 world cup season, and represented Finland at the Biathlon World Championships 2015 in Kontiolahti. ==References== == External links == * Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Finnish female biathletes
